# Disco Limerick

There once was a dancer named Sloan,
Whose disco moves were widely known.
    With sequins so bright,
    He danced through the night,
Till the DJ played "I Will Survive" on his own.

The disco ball spun with such flair,
As boogie-ers danced without care.
    In platforms so high,
    They reached for the sky,
With bell-bottoms flared and big hair.

When Saturday Night Fever broke,
The hustle became the new craze folk.
    From Studio 54,
    To dance floors galore,
The spirit of disco will never go broke.

